snippet.title: Meghan Markle: Mail on Sunday loses appeal bid | Esther Krakue and Mike Graham
snippet.description:
Meghan Markle wins latest privacy battle against Mail on Sunday

The Court of Appeal has dismissed an attempt by the Mail on Sunday's publisher to overturn a privacy decision over Meghan Markle's letter to her father.

The decision was upheld that Associated Newspapers breached the Duchess of Sussex's privacy after extracts of her letter were found in their paper, and that its contents were "private" and "not matters of legitimate public interest".

Associated Newspapers has expressed its "disappointment" at the decision and said it was considering a further appeal to the Supreme Court.

Broadcaster Esther Krakue has a question for Prince Harry: "What are you doing with this woman?"
